<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The documentation lists {{string}} as return type for Zend_Db_Select::assemble(). 
However, when calling assemble on a vanilla Zend_Db_Select object, the return value will be null.
This is due to _renderColumns() returning null when there is no columns set in the _parts array and all other _render* methods returning the $sql param untouched. The API docs could be improved to list {{string|null}} as return type for assemble() to reflect that.</p>

<p>With PHPUnit:
{{$statement = new Zend_Db_Select;}}
{{$sql              = $statement-&gt;assemble();}}
{{$this-&gt;assertTrue(is_string($sql));}}
will fail.</p>

    </div>
